  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Restoration of Wetland Buffer Zones in the Lower Sin&#xFA; River Watershed for Climate Change Adaptation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmers, Families, Fisher People</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to reduce the environmental and socioeconomic vulnerabilities of 609 rural families located in 5 municipalities in the wetland buffer zones of the lower watershed of the Sin&#xFA; River in C&#xF3;rdoba Department, Colombia, by increasing their resilience to climate change. Specifically, it will:

(1) Reduce the impact of droughts and floods for 559 families through the restoration of riparian buffer strips, the implementation of 30  family-level agroforestry systems in these areas, and the implementation of 6 collective agroforestry systems on elevated dikes; and
(2) Provide 50 families wiho suffer from inadquate water access due to saltwater intrusion with access to potable water through the construction of water capture systems and training in hygiene practices.</narrative>
  </description>
